ces Teach Act  Consulting Course Development First Day of Class Production Resources Teaching Online Technology Options Training Videoconferencing         Home » Teaching Support » CLEAR Copyright GuideLocate Usable Works Works in Multiple Formats   UNT Library resourceshttp://www.library.unt.edu/research Creative Commons Search http://search.creativecommons.org/ Search reliable sources for creative works including media, images, video, audio, music, web. Google Advanced Search https://support.google.com/websearch/answer/29508?hl=en Use the usage rights filter to find web content by category (such as text, videos, audio, or images) you can reuse, share, or modify. Getty Search Gateway http://search.getty.edu/gateway/landing Search across Getty repositories, including collections databases, library catalogs, and collection inventories to locate books, periodicals, photos, and more. Southern Connecticut State University \u2014 Open Access Resources http://libguides.southernct.edu/content.php?pid=69634&sid=515274 Search works including audio, video, images, journals, books, teaching materials, and mixed   Text   Project Gutenberghttp://gutenberg.org/wiki/Main_Page A collection of public domain electronic books. ManyBooks.net http://manybooks.net/ 29,000 free eBooks available for Kindle, Nook, iPad, and most other eReaders. Merlot http://merlot.org/merlot/index.htm  A free and open peer reviewed collection of online teaching and learning materials and faculty-developed services contributed and used by an international education community.   Video  Center for Media and Social Impacthttp://www.cmsimpact.org/fair-use/related-materials/codes/code-best-practices-fair-use-online-video Code of Best Practices in Fair Use for Online Video The Internet Archive \u2014 Prelinger Archives https://archive.org/details/prelinger A collection of advertising, educational, industrial, and amateur films  Audio  Librivoxhttps://librivox.org Public domain audio books  Images  Smithsonian Institution \u2014 Public Domain Imageshttp://flickr.com/photos/smithsonian Via Flickr Commons New York Times \u2014 Public Domain Images Archiveshttp://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Public_Domain_Images_from_the_New_York_Times Via Wikimedia Commons Google Search by Imagehttp://www.google.com/insidesearch/features/images/searchbyimage.html Search by image allows you to do a reverse image search, which means you start with an existing image and search for its source(s). FreeDigitalPhotoshttp://www.freedigitalphotos.net/ Search free stock photos and illustrations. Morgue Fileshttp://morguefile.com/license/morguefile Stock photos you are free to use and adapt without attributing the original author. National Gallery of Arthttps://images.nga.gov/en/page/openaccess.html The NGA has an open access policy for digital images of works of art believed to be in the public domain. Images are free of charge for any use, and users do not need seek permission. Images are available images.nga.gov. National Gallery of Arthttps://images.nga.gov/ This site provides 25,000 free and re-usable images of art, each accompanied by a snippet of information on the original artist. The British Libraryhttp://www.flickr.com/photos/britishlibrary Over a million images on Flickr Commons for anyone to use. Getty Open Content Programhttp://www.getty.edu/about/opencontent.html The Getty makes available to be used for any purpose, without charge or permission required, all available digital images to which the Getty holds the rights or that are in the public domain. Wellcome Images Libraryhttp://wellcomeimages.org/ Over 100,000 high resolution historical images including manuscripts, paintings, etchings, early photography, and advertisements are freely available& under the Creative Commons Attribution (CC-BY) licence, with an acknowledgement of the original source. Wikimedia Commons http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Main_Page  A database of millions of freely usable media files to which anyone can contribute. Harvard Law School: Finding Public Domain and Creative Commons Images http://guides.library.harvard.edu/finding_images This guide will help you find and correctly attribute public domain and Creative Commons images. Free Digital Photos.Net  http://www.freedigitalphotos.net/  Download free and premium stock photos and illustrations produced by our community of professional stock photographers and digital illustrators. MorgueFile http://morguefile.com/license/morguefile Free photos you're free to adapt, use for commercial purposes, without attribution, under the following conditions: You cannot sell, license, sublicense, rent, transfer or distribute this image exactly as it is without alteration, and you may not claim ownership of this image in its original state, or you can receive permission to use from the owner.                  Contact Faculty Helpdesk: Email: clearhelp@unt.edu Phone: (940) 369-7394 In-person: Chilton Hall 112C Site Support: For questions and comments concerning website functionality, please contact: Gabe.Vega@unt.edu             Physical Address:      Center for Learning Enhancement, Assessment, and Redesign     410 Avenue C Chilton Hall 112 Denton, TX 76203 USA  Voice: 940.565.2708                 UNT System:  UNT Home UNT System UNT Dallas UNT Health Science Center               Site last updated on March 09, 2017  Disclaimer |        AA/EOE/ADA |        Privacy Statement |        Web Accessibility Policy |        State of Texas Online |        Emergency Preparedness               
